  "title": "What Does Sanctuary Mean to Me, at Home?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for clarifying what your home needs to feel like refuge",
  "excerpt": "A set of journal prompts for the woman who knows her home should feel like sanctuary but cannot name what that would actually require. Moves from the broad feeling to the specific conditions that create or block it.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education, drawing on intentional homemaking writing and the slow-living tradition.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal prompt set for the gap between what a home is supposed to give and what yours currently does. The prompts move from a wide first look at the idea of sanctuary down to the specific, small conditions that would make it real in your particular house.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal prompts? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I walk into my home right now, what is the first thing I feel?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Not what you think you should feel. What you actually feel. Write it without editing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does the word 'sanctuary' bring up for me?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A place, a feeling, an image. Write whatever comes first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there one room or corner that already feels like sanctuary to me?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If yes: what does that space have that the rest of the house doesn't? If no: what would need to change for one such place to exist?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is the biggest thing that makes my home feel less like refuge?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is it noise? Mess? The to-do list you see everywhere? The feeling of work never finishing? Name it specifically.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is one small, free, doable thing that would make it feel more like sanctuary?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Not a renovation. Not a holiday. One thing you could do this week.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Written for homemade.education. Draws on the slow-living and intentional homemaking traditions. Both treat the home as a daily practice, not a backdrop.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
